```

| Field | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `userName` | `String` | Stores the username entered during registration |
| `password` | `String` | Stores the password entered during registration |
| `firstName` | `String` (`final`) | Hard-coded first name used in the welcome message |
| `lastName` | `String` (`final`) | Hard-coded last name used in the welcome message |
| `cellPhoneNumber` | `String` | Stores the cell number entered during registration |

**Why `private`?** These fields can only be changed through the class's own methods â€” this is *encapsulation*. Outside classes (like `Main.java`) cannot directly overwrite a user's password or username; they must go through `registerUser()`.

**Why `final` on `firstName` and `lastName`?** These never change once set, so marking them `final` documents that intent and prevents accidental modification later in the class.

