## 4. `checkCellPhoneNumber()`

```java
public boolean checkCellPhoneNumber() {
    return cellPhoneNumber != null && cellPhoneNumber.matches("^\\+27\\d{9}$");
}
```

**Rule:** The cell number must be in South African international format: `+27` followed by exactly 9 digits (12 characters total).

**How the regex works:**
| Symbol | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `^` | Start of the string |
| `\\+27` | Literally matches `+27` |
| `\\d{9}` | Exactly 9 digits |
| `$` | End of the string |

**Examples:**
| Number | Matches? | Valid? |
