## How `Main.java` uses this class

```java
Login1 auth = new Login1();

// Registration
String result = auth.registerUser(username, password, phone);
System.out.println(result);

// Login
String loginResult = auth.returnLoginStatus(loginUser, loginPass);
System.out.println(loginResult);

// Gatekeeping â€” only continue into QuickChat if login actually succeeded
if (!auth.loginUser(loginUser, loginPass)) {
    System.out.println("Login failed. Exiting.");
    return;
}
```

This shows the typical pattern: `registerUser()` is called once at the start, then `returnLoginStatus()` is used for the printed message, while `loginUser()` (the boolean version) is used separately to actually **gate** access to the rest of the program.

